This paper deals with 3D surface reconstruction from 2D images, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for this task suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of synthetic datasets, which is a common technique in graphics (cs.GR). The use of adversarial learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The problem of non-rigid 3D reconstruction could also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
